#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn6.4"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn6.4:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 6 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 6 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn6.4:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga "
msgstr "1. The Appeal "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 4. Bakabrahmasutta → bakasuttaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "sn6.4:0.3"
msgid "4. Bakabrahmasutta "
msgstr "4. With Baka the Brahmā "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn6.4:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "sn6.4:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn6.4:1.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bakassa brahmuno evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "Now at that time Baka the Brahmā had the following harmful misconception: "

# NOTE: This is the Upanishadic view; cp SN 22.81
#. VAR: uttari → uttariṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn6.4:1.4"
msgid "“idaṃ niccaṃ, idaṃ dhuvaṃ, idaṃ sassataṃ, idaṃ kevalaṃ, idaṃ acavanadhammaṃ, idañhi na jāyati na jīyati na mīyati na cavati na upapajjati, ito ca panaññaṃ uttari nissaraṇaṃ natthī”ti. "
msgstr "“This is permanent, this is everlasting, this is eternal, this is whole, this is imperishable. For this is where there’s no being born, growing old, dying, passing away, or being reborn. And there’s no other escape beyond this.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.311, sc2
msgctxt "sn6.4:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā bakassa brahmuno cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya—seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—jetavane antarahito tasmiṃ brahmaloke pāturahosi. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha knew what Baka the Brahmā was thinking. As easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, he vanished from Jeta’s Grove and reappeared in that Brahmā realm. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn6.4:2.2"
msgid "Addasā kho bako brahmā bhagavantaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ. "
msgstr "Baka the Brahmā saw the Buddha coming off in the distance "

msgctxt "sn6.4:2.3"
msgid "Disvāna bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "and said to him, "

msgctxt "sn6.4:2.4"
msgid "“ehi kho, mārisa, svāgataṃ te, mārisa. "
msgstr "“Come, good sir! Welcome, good sir! "

msgctxt "sn6.4:2.5"
msgid "Cirassaṃ kho, mārisa, imaṃ pariyāyamakāsi yadidaṃ idhāgamanāya. "
msgstr "It’s been a long time since you took the opportunity to come here. "

msgctxt "sn6.4:2.6"
msgid "Idañhi, mārisa, niccaṃ, idaṃ dhuvaṃ, idaṃ sassataṃ, idaṃ kevalaṃ, idaṃ acavanadhammaṃ, idañhi na jāyati na jīyati na mīyati na cavati na upapajjati. Ito ca panaññaṃ uttari nissaraṇaṃ natthī”ti. "
msgstr "For this is permanent, this is everlasting, this is eternal, this is complete, this is imperishable. For this is where there’s no being born, growing old, dying, passing away, or being reborn. And there’s no other escape beyond this.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.143, sc3
msgctxt "sn6.4:3.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhagavā bakaṃ brahmānaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he had spoken, the Buddha said to him, "

msgctxt "sn6.4:3.2"
msgid "“avijjāgato vata bho bako brahmā, avijjāgato vata bho bako brahmā. "
msgstr "“Alas, Baka the Brahmā is lost in ignorance! Alas, Baka the Brahmā is lost in ignorance! "

msgctxt "sn6.4:3.3"
msgid "Yatra hi nāma aniccaṃyeva samānaṃ niccanti vakkhati, adhuvaṃyeva samānaṃ dhuvanti vakkhati, asassataṃyeva samānaṃ sassatanti vakkhati, akevalaṃyeva samānaṃ kevalanti vakkhati, cavanadhammaṃyeva samānaṃ acavanadhammanti vakkhati. "
msgstr "Because what is actually impermanent, not lasting, transient, incomplete, and perishable, he says is permanent, everlasting, eternal, complete, and imperishable. "

msgctxt "sn6.4:3.4"
msgid "Yattha ca pana jāyati ca jīyati ca mīyati ca cavati ca upapajjati ca, tañca tathā vakkhati: "
msgstr "And where there is being born, growing old, dying, passing away, and being reborn, he says that "

msgctxt "sn6.4:3.5"
msgid "‘idañhi na jāyati na jīyati na mīyati na cavati na upapajjati’. "
msgstr "there’s no being born, growing old, dying, passing away, or being reborn. "

msgctxt "sn6.4:3.6"
msgid "Santañca panaññaṃ uttari nissaraṇaṃ, ‘natthaññaṃ uttari nissaraṇan’ti vakkhatī”ti. "
msgstr "And although there is another escape beyond this, he says that there’s no other escape beyond this.” "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.312, sc4
msgctxt "sn6.4:4.1"
msgid "“Dvāsattati gotama puññakammā, "
msgstr "“Gotama, we seventy-two merit-makers are now wielders of power, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.4:4.2"
msgid "Vasavattino jātijaraṃ atītā; "
msgstr "having passed beyond rebirth and old age. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.4:4.3"
msgid "Ayamantimā vedagū brahmupapatti, "
msgstr "This is our last rebirth as Brahmā, knowledge-master. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.4:4.4"
msgid "Asmābhijappanti janā anekā”ti. "
msgstr "And now many people pray to us.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn6.4:5.1"
msgid "“Appañhi etaṃ na hi dīghamāyu, "
msgstr "“But, Baka, the life span here is short, not long, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.4:5.2"
msgid "Yaṃ tvaṃ baka maññasi dīghamāyuṃ; "
msgstr "though you think it’s long. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: sahassānaṃ → sahassāna (s1-3, km, pts2)
msgctxt "sn6.4:5.3"
msgid "Sataṃ sahassānaṃ nirabbudānaṃ, "
msgstr "I know that your life span "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.4:5.4"
msgid "Āyuṃ pajānāmi tavāhaṃ brahme”ti. "
msgstr "is two quinquadecillion years, Brahmā.” "

# NOTE: I disagree with BB and comm here. The phrasing ahamasmi is absolutely characteristic of brahma and not of the Buddha. If Brahma asks a question later on he’s either testing the Buddha, or more likely, being made to look the fool.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn6.4:6.1"
msgid "“Anantadassī bhagavāhamasmi, "
msgstr "“Blessed One, I am the one of infinite vision, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.4:6.2"
msgid "Jātijaraṃ sokamupātivatto; "
msgstr "who has gone beyond rebirth and old age and sorrow. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.4:6.3"
msgid "Kiṃ me purāṇaṃ vatasīlavattaṃ, "
msgstr "What precepts and observances did I practice in the past? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.4:6.4"
msgid "Ācikkha me taṃ yamahaṃ vijaññā”ti. "
msgstr "Explain to me so I can understand.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.313, sc7
msgctxt "sn6.4:7.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ tvaṃ apāyesi bahū manusse, "
msgstr "“You gave drink to many people "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.4:7.2"
msgid "Pipāsite ghammani samparete; "
msgstr "who were oppressed by thirst and heat. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.4:7.3"
msgid "Taṃ te purāṇaṃ vatasīlavattaṃ, "
msgstr "They’re the precepts and observances you practiced in the past. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.4:7.4"
msgid "Suttappabuddhova anussarāmi. "
msgstr "I recollect it like one who has wakened from sleep. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn6.4:8.1"
msgid "Yaṃ eṇikūlasmiṃ janaṃ gahītaṃ, "
msgstr "When people at Deer River Bank were seized, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.4:8.2"
msgid "Amocayī gayhakaṃ nīyamānaṃ; "
msgstr "you released the captives as they were led away. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.4:8.3"
msgid "Taṃ te purāṇaṃ vatasīlavattaṃ, "
msgstr "That’s the precepts and observances you practiced in the past. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.4:8.4"
msgid "Suttappabuddhova anussarāmi. "
msgstr "I recollect it like one who has wakened from sleep. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn6.4:9.1"
msgid "Gaṅgāya sotasmiṃ gahītanāvaṃ, "
msgstr "When a boat on the Ganges River was seized "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.4:9.2"
msgid "Luddena nāgena manussakamyā; "
msgstr "by a fierce dragon desiring human flesh, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.4:9.3"
msgid "Pamocayittha balasā pasayha, "
msgstr "you freed it wielding mighty force. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.4:9.4"
msgid "Taṃ te purāṇaṃ vatasīlavattaṃ; "
msgstr "That’s the precepts and observances you practiced in the past. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.4:9.5"
msgid "Suttappabuddhova anussarāmi. "
msgstr "I recollect it like one who has wakened from sleep. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.144, sc10
msgctxt "sn6.4:10.1"
msgid "Kappo ca te baddhacaro ahosiṃ, "
msgstr "I used to be your servant named Kappa. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Sambuddhimantaṃ → sambuddhivantaṃ (si, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "sn6.4:10.2"
msgid "Sambuddhimantaṃ vatinaṃ amaññi; "
msgstr "You thought he was intelligent and loyal. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.4:10.3"
msgid "Taṃ te purāṇaṃ vatasīlavattaṃ, "
msgstr "That’s the precepts and observances you practiced in the past. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.4:10.4"
msgid "Suttappabuddhova anussarāmī”ti. "
msgstr "I recollect it like one who has wakened from sleep.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.314, sc11
msgctxt "sn6.4:11.1"
msgid "“Addhā pajānāsi mametamāyuṃ, "
msgstr "“You certainly understand this life span of mine. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Aññepi → aññampi (bj, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn6.4:11.2"
msgid "Aññepi jānāsi tathā hi buddho; "
msgstr "And others, too, you know; that’s why you’re the Buddha. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.4:11.3"
msgid "Tathā hi tyāyaṃ jalitānubhāvo, "
msgstr "And that’s why your blazing glory "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.4:11.4"
msgid "Obhāsayaṃ tiṭṭhati brahmalokan”ti. "
msgstr "lights up even the Brahmā realm.”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
